      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Grammy for Indians</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By ROBBIE WOLIVER</byline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The board of trustees of the Recording Academy announced last week that American Indians would be represented in the Grammys.</p>
        <p>After a three-year lobbying effort by Ellen Bello, founder of the Native American Music Awards and the Native American Music Association, a Best Native American Music Album award will be presented next year.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The board of trustees of the Recording Academy announced last week that American Indians would be represented in the Grammys.</p>
        <p>After a three-year lobbying effort by Ellen Bello, founder of the Native American Music Awards and the Native American Music Association, a Best Native American Music Album award will be presented next year.</p>
        <p>Ms. Bello, of Dix Hills, said, ''This is so long overdue, but I'm thankful all that hard work paid off.''</p>
        <p>ROBBIE WOLIVER</p>
      </block>
